```json
{
  "summary": "Add Web App Manifest and Service Worker to make the single-file todo app installable and fully offline-capable as a PWA",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "title": "Create Web App Manifest (manifest.json)",
      "description": "Create a manifest.json file at the project root with all required PWA fields: name ('My Todo List'), short_name, start_url ('./'), display ('standalone'), theme_color, background_color, and an icons array referencing 192×192 and 512×512 PNG/SVG icon files. No external URLs."
    },
    {
      "title": "Generate PWA icon files",
      "description": "Create two SVG icon files (icon-192.svg and icon-512.svg) representing the app logo — a simple checklist/checkmark motif using the app's blue (#4a90e2) brand color. Reference both in manifest.json with the correct size and type fields. These must be self-contained with no external resources."
    },
    {
      "title": "Create Service Worker (sw.js) with cache-first offline strategy",
      "description": "Create sw.js that on install caches the app shell: index.html, manifest.json, icon-192.svg, icon-512.svg. On fetch, serve from cache first and fall back to network. Use a versioned cache name (e.g. 'todo-v1') and clean up old caches on activate. Must not request any external URLs — all cached URLs are same-origin only."
    },
    {
      "title": "Wire up PWA support in index.html",
      "description": "In the <head> of index.html: add <link rel='manifest' href='manifest.json'>, <meta name='theme-color' content='#4a90e2'>, <meta name='apple-mobile-web-app-capable' content='yes'>, <meta name='apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style'>, and <link rel='apple-touch-icon' href='icon-192.svg'>. At the end of <body>, add an inline <script> block that registers sw.js via navigator.serviceWorker.register('./sw.js') guarded by feature detection."
    }
  ]
}
```
